def: A "tear-bottle;" a narrow-necked vessel found in sepulchers ofthe ancient Romans; -- so called from a former notion that the tearsof the deceased person's friends were collected in it. Called alsolachrymal or lacrymal.
Not corrigible; incapable of being corrected or amended; badbeyond correction; irreclaimable; as, incorrigible error."Incorrigible fools." Dryden.
One who is skilled in or practices microtomy.
A vessel of war carrying guns on three decks.
The use or application of a caustic; cautery. Ferrand.
A blank book in which extracts cut from books and papers may bepasted and kept.
